subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Head and pronotum dark reddish brown; base of elytra similarly colored but lightening posteriorly (
Fig. 1, 4
); head and pronotum glabrous, shiny, with moderately sized punctures fairly evenly spaced, well defined; clypeus distinctly but not deeply emarginate, apex moderately upturned (
Fig. 1
); frontoclypeal suture well defined and impressed; base of the elytra and elytral suture with sparse, erect setae; antennae with 9 antennomeres, antennal club slightly longer than scape.
